data.title: Dubai's higher education enrolments to surge by 40% by 2030, study reveals. Dubai Academic City and Knowledge Park report high demand at Going Global conference.
data.description: A recent study conducted by Dubai International Academic City and Dubai Knowledge Park, both under TECOM Group PJSC, reveals a significant demand for the city's diverse academic programs. These leading higher education and lifelong learning centers presented their findings in a white paper at the Going Global conference. This exclusive study showcases the growing interest in Dubai's academic pathways, emphasizing the need for more educational opportunities in the region. The research sheds light on the increasing number of individuals seeking a wide range of programs offered by these institutions, indicating a strong demand for quality education options in Dubai.

data.title: SEGG Media plans $300M Web3 strategy to tokenize sports and entertainment, crypto treasury, crypto advisory board, and acquisitions.
data.description: SEGG Media Corporation (NASDAQ: SEGG), formerly known as Lottery.com Inc., has unveiled its Web3 and Digital Asset Strategy, a comprehensive two-year plan aimed at creating sustainable on-chain yield, advancing tokenization in sports and entertainment, and integrating blockchain infrastructure into its global media network. This announcement follows the establishment of the SEGG Media Crypto Advisory Board, tasked with overseeing governance, risk management, and implementation of the company's $300 million Digital Asset and Tokenization Program. Key to SEGG's strategy is an 80/20 capital allocation approach, with 80% of funds dedicated to a diversified multi-asset crypto treasury focused on Bitcoin (CRYPTO: BTC) for validator-based income, along with Ethereum (CRYPTO: ETH), Solana (CRYPTO: SOL), and ZIGChain (CRYPTO: ZIG). The remaining 20% will be allocated towards strategic acquisitions. This initiative signifies SEGG Media's expansion into the digital asset space and its commitment to driving innovation within the industry.

data.title: Dogness revenue up 39.5% to $20.7M, loss narrows to $5.1M. Stock down 75%. Founder started from shoelace factory. Pet tech boosts hopes.
data.description: Dogness, a pet product seller, has seen a 39.5% increase in revenue to $20.7 million in its fiscal year through June, while its loss narrowed by 15.8% to $5.1 million. The company's shares have dropped by 75% since the start of the year despite strong growth in smart products. Chen Silong, the founder, started the company in 2008 after previously working in industries like shoelace production and carabiners. The rise of China's pet economy, especially among millennials and GenZ, has driven demand for pet products. The company went public in 2017 and saw success in 2022 due to the pandemic's effect on pet adoption. However, recent declines in revenue and share prices have affected Dogness negatively. With the emergence of high-tech pet products, there is potential for the company's recovery as shown in its latest annual results.

data.title: Western Digital's Q1 earnings likely to decrease with estimated $1.58 per share, revenue $2.73 billion, down from $4.09 billion.
data.description: Western Digital Corporation (NASDAQ: WDC) is set to announce its first-quarter earnings after markets close on Thursday, Oct. 30. Analysts predict earnings of $1.58 per share, a decrease from $1.78 per share a year ago. Revenue for the quarter is estimated to be $2.73 billion, down from $4.09 billion in the previous year. In the fourth quarter, Western Digital surpassed expectations and provided first-quarter guidance that exceeded estimates. Following this news, the company's shares rose by 13.2% to $141.38. For more detailed information, readers can visit Benzinga.com.

data.title: Cleveland-Cliffs partners with POSCO under MoU, Korea's largest steelmaker; agreement signed on Sept 17, 2025.
data.description: Cleveland-Cliffs Inc. (NYSE: CLF) has announced a strategic partnership with POSCO, Korea's largest steelmaker and the world's third-largest steelmaker outside of China. The Memorandum of Understanding (MoU) between the two companies was signed on September 17, 2025. This collaboration follows the recent finalization of the new U.S. and Korea trade agreement, signaling enhanced cooperation between the industrial sectors of both nations. This partnership marks a significant development in the steel industry, with Cleveland-Cliffs Inc. positioning itself strategically in the global market.

data.title: Roblox's Q3 2025 financial results released, showcasing company's performance.
data.description: A recent report states that the global economy is expected to grow by approximately 3.5% this year, following a 3% growth in the previous year. The growth is mainly driven by strong performances in major economies such as the United States, China, and India. However, concerns about trade tensions and geopolitical uncertainties remain key risks to this optimistic outlook. In contrast, the Eurozone is projected to experience a more modest growth rate of around 1.5% amid ongoing challenges within the region. This disparity in growth rates among different regions highlights the uneven nature of the global economic recovery. Despite positive growth forecasts, experts warn that factors such as inflation rates, unemployment levels, and government policies could impact the overall economic stability in the near future.

data.title: Estée Lauder beats Q1 expectations with $3.481B in sales (+4% YoY), plans profits with $2.551B gross profit.(Collectors: 7,000 job cuts, 32 cents EPS, 17 cents expected EPS).
data.description: Estée Lauder Companies Inc. saw a significant rise in premarket trading after surpassing first-quarter expectations and confirming its 2026 sales forecast. The company reported adjusted earnings per share of 32 cents compared to the estimated 17 cents, with quarterly sales reaching $3.481 billion, a 4% increase from last year. Organic net sales climbed 3% year-over-year to $3.455 billion. Skin care sales rose by 3% to $1.58 billion, makeup dipped by 2% to $1.03 billion due to Bobbi Brown's underperformance, while fragrance sales spiked 13% to $721 million. Adjusted gross profit rose by 4% to $2.551 billion, with a 60 basis point increase in adjusted gross margin to 73.3%. The company's various beauty categories saw mixed performance, with fragrance and skin care performing well, offset by makeup and haircare struggling. Margins were boosted by Profit Recovery and Growth initiatives.

data.title: CMS subsidiary, Dermavon, gains NDA acceptance for AD indication of MG-K10 in China, intended for adult treatment.
data.description: On October 30, 2025, China Medical System Holdings Limited (CMS) shared exciting news about its subsidiary, Dermavon Holdings Limited, an innovative pharmaceutical company focusing on skin health. Dermavon is seeking a separate listing on the Main Board of The Stock Exchange of Hong Kong Limited. The company, along with its subsidiaries, has co-development rights (excluding atopic dermatitis) and exclusive commercialization rights for the Class 1 innovative drug MG-K10, a humanized monoclonal antibody injection targeting anti-IL-4Rα. The National Medical Products Administration accepted the New Drug Application (NDA) for MG-K10 on the same day. This product aims to treat adults with moderate-to-severe atopic dermatitis who have inadequate control with topical therapies or for whom such treatments are not recommended. Further details were provided in CMS’s announcement on April 22, 2025.

data.title: CIBC Innovation Banking funds zLinq with growth capital for telecom solutions, introducing new product Telfinity.
data.description: In Denver, CIBC Innovation Banking has disclosed that they have extended growth financing to assist zLinq, a prominent provider of telecommunications lifecycle management solutions for enterprise customers. zLinq aids IT departments in the selection, deployment, management, and optimization of telecommunications, encompassing voice and data assets. The funding will facilitate the creation of a fresh product, Telfinity, designed to establish an abstraction layer connecting intricate telecom providers with IT teams. This move by CIBC will empower enterprises to enhance their telecommunications operations.
